  "text": "In the opposite case where a liquid, i.e., cyclohexane is able to wet the pore surface of a mica capillary, the contact angle can assume < 90 ° , and the liquid would condense under confinement. Evaporation will take place if the pore widens again, and the relative pressure is alleviated [CITATION_1] .",
